claim.claim-text:
A document binder for bonding with at least one book (20), the book (20) including a spine portion (24), comprising:
a cover (110) including a front cover (112a), a back cover (112b) and a back board (114) disposed between the front cover (112a) and the back cover (112b), wherein the back board (114) includes a base plate (114a) pivotally connecting the front cover (112a) and the back cover (112b) and allowing the front and back covers (112a, 112b) pivoting there-toward;
a holding base (120) secured on the back board (114) while immobile thereon, the holding base (120) including an upper face (120a) and a lower face (120b) opposing the upper face (120a), the lower face (120b) disposed between the upper face (120a) and the back board (114);
a first holding member (150) disposed on one end of the holding base (120) and projecting there-from;
a second holding member (160) disposed on the other end of the holding base (120) and projecting there-from; and
at least one rod (130) going through the spine portion (24), the two ends of the rods (130) retained by the first holding member (150) and second holding member (160) respectively.
